- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper may be relevant to game theory as the Disjoint Paths problem has applications in network routing and communication, which are important in game theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may be relevant to computational complexity as it proposes a linear-time algorithm for the Planar Disjoint Paths problem, which is a non-trivial result and may have implications for the complexity of related problems.
